Author: jl777c#5810
Content: pushed to dev branch a very significant new flag and bug fix!

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: all orders now support a "fill":1 flag, if set the order must fill 100% the volume specified. since many people complained about this (even if they got a better price) it should reduce complaints, alice has utxos

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: while implemeting it for bobside, I realized that somewhere along the way, bob scanning of smaller sized trades was lost! So I now have bob scanning smaller and smaller trade sizes if he cant fill the full order (only if fill:0 which will be the default for any older versions)

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: from what I see bob not filling partial orders is the main cause for people not being able to ordermatch. the other is networking troubles, especially on windows. current fix wont change that but being able to  ordermatch partials will increase ordermatch (and user complaints that the full order didnt complete). Before alice was operatng as fill:0 and bob as fill:1

Author: jl777c#5810
Content:
from the user point of view alice.fill.0/bob.fill.1 would likely look very similar to alice.fill.0/bob.fill.0
of course until all the bobs update, we wont see the full effect. updating my bobs

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: they are all updated

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: i think the reason we didnt find this was alice doing the partial fills (Scanning for utxo that fit) made it so partial fills were normal and the assumption was bob was also doing fill:0

Author: jl777c#5810
Content:
thre is fill and gtc now:
fill:0 gtc:0 <- how it behaved before, basically an immediate or cancel order
fill:1 gtc:0 is a fill or kill order
fill:1 gtc:1 is probably the thing to do for a default
fill:0 gtc:1 will stop as soon as any part of the order is done

also as soon as a trade starts, it basically cancels the gtc
